From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 10:50:15 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add default-disabled GRX Route B rd_native cluster_store
 in-frame store replacement

Stacked on 0001..0029 + 0040 + 0041 + 0042 + 0043 (the branch-HEAD gpu_culling
tail plus the tonemap, ssao_blur, taa_resolve and particles_copy rd_native
slices). This is the fifth Route B REAL replacement pass and turns GRX-014 from
the patch 0025 SCAFFOLD (native continuation/backstop) into a genuine in-frame
replacement: Route B drives the Rurix cluster_store kernel as a first-class
in-frame RenderingDevice compute dispatch for the cluster merge (pack) segment,
instead of the out-of-frame rxgd shim bridge, and when it records the native
Godot cluster_store dispatch is genuinely skipped (one fewer native dispatch; no
scaffold clear, unlike patch 0025).

- drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h: new default-false virtual
  try_record_cluster_store_rd_native(int64_t compute_list, RID cluster_render,
  RID render_elements, RID cluster_store, Size2i screen_size,
  const uint8_t *push_constants, uint32_t push_constant_bytes). It takes the
  Godot ComputeListID of the ALREADY-OPEN bake_cluster store compute list
  (bake_cluster opens one list around the store dispatch, so rd_native must NOT
  begin/end its own) plus the three Godot structured-buffer RID handles in the
  container's binding order (cluster_render = SRV t0, render_elements = SRV t1,
  cluster_store = UAV u0) instead of the native ID3D12Resource* handles the
  shim-path try_record_cluster_store takes. Base returns false.
- modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp: two new default-safe settings,
  independent of the four existing cluster_store shim settings (untouched):
  rendering/rurix_accel/passes/cluster_store/backend (int, default 0;
  0=disabled / 1=shim / 2=rd_native) and
  rendering/rurix_accel/passes/cluster_store/rd_container_path (string, default
  ""). Defaults keep the RD-native path disabled.
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.{h,cpp}: try_record_cluster_store_rd_native
  override. Lazily builds the compute pipeline once (FileAccess reads the Rurix
  container -> shader_create_from_bytecode -> compute_pipeline_create, latching
  rd_native_cluster_store_load_failed on any failure so it is not retried per
  frame), binds t0=cluster_render, t1=render_elements and u0=cluster_store via
  UniformSetCacheRD all as UNIFORM_TYPE_STORAGE_BUFFER (the buffer probe proved
  RAW == structured equivalence at zero tolerance), passes the 32-byte
  ClusterStore::PushConstant b0 mirror verbatim, and records a screen-size
  dispatch onto the caller's compute list (compute_list_dispatch_threads divides
  by the container's 8x8 local size). No submit()/sync() (a local-RD-only
  concept). The one-shot RXGD_RD_NATIVE_CLUSTER_STORE active marker is emitted via
  print_verbose when the pipeline is first built (not per-frame).
- servers/rendering/renderer_rd/cluster_builder_rd.cpp bake_cluster: in the store
  segment, backend == 2 runs the rd_native gate BEFORE the shim gate; a successful
  record skips both the shim gate and the native cluster_store dispatch. backend
  != 2 leaves the pre-existing shim/native chain byte-for-byte unchanged.

Fail-closed everywhere: with the default backend == 0 (and empty container path),
rd_native is never engaged and the native Godot cluster store renders. Only the
compute merge (store) segment routes through rd_native; the cluster_render raster
segment, the buffer clears, and the render_element_count == 0 early-out stay
native permanently. RXGD_ABI_VERSION is unchanged (this path does not touch the C
ABI struct layout and sets no RxGdCaps.flags bit; rd_native is bridge-
independent). No performance claim is made.
